data.name: Wealth Builder Investor Loan
data.description: Make your investment work harder for you with low fixed and variable interest rates, and the option to add an offset account.

features.additionalInfo: Yes - fee free redraw available via Internet Banking (min $500) – available on variable loans only.
A valuation is required for a loan top up.

Switching is a change to one or more aspects of your loan's terms and conditions, for example switching from a variable rate to a fixed rate or switching from Interest Only payments to Principal and Interest repayments.
Splitting is when you divide one loan into two or more loan accounts, generally with different loan types, repayment types or interest rates. We allow this with up to 4 splits per loan.
This is required for loans above 80% LVR.
100% offset available on variable rate loans, no offset facility available on fixed rate loans.

We’ve made it easier than ever to access and manage your money. Manage your money on the go with our mobile banking app, or login to internet banking to manage your account, view your transactions, transfer funds and more. We also offer phone banking and SMS banking.

features.additionalValue: Additional repayments and Early Repayment Adjustment
features.additionalInfo: Unlimited additional repayments and early repayments (discharge fee may apply) when on variable rate home loans. You may make up to $10,000 of additional payments a year on fixed rate loans (anything above may incur a fee). Early loan payout on a fixed rate loan may result in break costs being charged.

eligibility.additionalValue: You must be an Australian citizen or permanent Australian resident that resides in Australia.
eligibility.additionalInfo: You must be an Australian citizen or permanent Australian resident that resides in Australia.
To apply you need to be 18 years of age or over.

fees.name: Establishment fee
fees.additionalInfo: Payable on all new loans. This fee covers the cost of property valuation (for one residential property up to $1.5M) and preparation of the loan documents. The fee also covers for the cost of up to 3 bank cheques used for settlement disbursements. Additional bank cheques will be charged the published bank cheque fee cost. Please note: Valuation for any residential property with an expected value above $1.5M will be charged as per the cost to us.

fees.name: Discharge fee
fees.additionalInfo: Payable when the security on your property is released. This fee covers our costs of preparing the necessary documentation to allow the discharge of your mortgage or other security type. Statutory government registration fees will also apply. Fee does not include settlement agent fees in non-CBD locations, which will be charged additionally as per cost to us.

fees.name: Loan re-documentation fee
fees.additionalInfo: Payable if the loan documents need to be reprepared due to a change in requirement by the customer. This fee also applies should you not proceed with the loan after the new loan contract is prepared.

fees.name: Loan top up fee
fees.additionalInfo: Payable when additional funds are requested under an existing mortgage. This fee covers administration costs where there is no change to the security or borrowers. Please note: Full valuation required for a loan top up will be charged as per the cost to us.

fees.name: Change of security fee
fees.additionalInfo: Payable when you wish to change security against your Home Loan with another security that is currently mortgaged to Australian Unity. If discharge of existing security is required, the discharge of mortgage fee will also be payable

fees.name: Additional valuation fee
fees.additionalInfo: Payable for any additional valuation required as part of the loan settlement process. Covers valuation for a residential property valued up to $1.5M. Please note: Valuation for any residential property with an expected value above $1.5M will be charged as per the cost to us.

fees.name: Loan restructure fee
fees.additionalInfo: Payable when the loan requires restructuring e.g. when a loan is changed from having two account holders to one account holder. Discharge of mortgage fee will also apply if a discharge and lodgement of a new mortgage are required. Yes on variable (interest only during construction period). N/A on fixed rate loan (can fix after construction period ends)

fees.name: Construction Loan
fees.additionalInfo: This fee includes property valuations at up to 5 stages of construction and up to 5 progress payments. Additional valuations or progress payments will be charged the standard published fees

fees.name: Additional payments
fees.additionalInfo: Payable for every progress payment made after the 5 progress payments covered in the construction loan fee.

fees.name: Bank cheque fee
fees.additionalInfo: Payable when additional bank cheques are required as part of the settlement process.

fees.name: Title/documentation production fee
fees.additionalInfo: Payable per occurrence of title production request. Statutory government fees will also apply.

fees.name: Preparation of Deed of Priority
fees.additionalInfo: Payable per occurrence of preparation of deed of priority.

fees.name: Product switch fee
fees.additionalInfo: Payable to cover associated administrative costs when switching between loan products.

fees.name: Interest type switch fee
fees.additionalInfo: Payable when you request to change your loan interest rate type e.g. Interest Only to Principal and Interest or vice versa and/or Variable to Fixed Interest Rate or vice versa.

fees.name: Staff assisted redraw
fees.additionalInfo: Payable when a redraw request is manually performed by a staff member.

fees.name: Audit request fee
fees.additionalInfo: $30 per hour (min charge $30). Charged when you request us to provide a written confirmation of your financial accounts with Australian Unity.

fees.name: Documentation search fee
fees.additionalInfo: $30 per hour (min charge $15). Charged when you request us to search and/or retrieve voucher/s or other documentation connected to your accounts with Australian Unity.

fees.name: Fixed interest rate lock fee - Investor Principal & Interest
fees.additionalInfo: 0.15% of the approved fixed loan amount with a minimum fee of $499.

fees.name: Fixed interest rate lock fee - Investor Interest Only
fees.additionalInfo: 0.15% of the approved fixed loan amount with a minimum fee of $499.
